article.description: Justin Tuoyo scored 15 points and Tre' McLean added 12 points and 10 rebounds as Chattanooga defeated Samford 63-56 Saturday night.
article.headline: Chattanooga upends Samford 63-56 behind Tuoyo and McLean
article.linkText: Chattanooga upends Samford 63-56 behind Tuoyo and McLean
article.story: HOMEWOOD, Ala. -- Justin Tuoyo scored 15 points and Tre' McLean added 12 points and 10 rebounds as Chattanooga defeated Samford 63-56 Saturday night. Chuck Ester's jumper early in the second half gave the Mocs a 37-28 lead. Samford then put together a 7-0 run on layups from Darius Jones-Gibson and Christen Cunningham, a Wyatt Walker jumper and a free throw from Jones-Gibson to cut the lead to two. But the Mocs' Dee Oldham made back-to-back 3s, and on his third 3 attempt he got fouled and made one of three to push the lead to 44-37. Tuoyo made a layup with 12:22 left, and two minutes later Duke Ethridge's dunk extended the lead to 48-37 for Chattanooga (18-3, 7-1). Samford then went on a 14-6 run to reduce the lead to three but could get no closer. Cunningham led Samford (11-11, 2-7) with 15 points and Jones-Gibson added 14.
